<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
Recently described species from Wuyi Mountains of Fujian Province. Head brown, wider than pronotum; ocelli pale brown; antennae and palpi light brown; pronotum brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F8002504" captionText="Figure 11. Rhopalopsole trichiotoma Yang &amp; Du, 2021. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view. Modified from Yang et al. 2021." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711855" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">11</figureCitation>
A). Tergum 10 bearing a large central plate covered with a sensilla basiconica patch in the two oval areas. Epiproct thick at base, ending in a shallow trilobed process (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F8002504" captionText="Figure 11. Rhopalopsole trichiotoma Yang &amp; Du, 2021. A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view. Modified from Yang et al. 2021." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711855" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
